Turkish Opposition Leader Says Under Surveillance, Hurriyet Says

-- B y   M a r k   B e n t l e y
-- 
2011-02-17T06:39:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/turkish-opposition-leader-says-under-surveillance-hurriyet-says.html
Kemal Kilicdaroglu, the chief of  Turkey ’s main opposition party, said people are listening to his
family’s phone calls, making it difficult for him to carry out
his duties and infringing on his private life, Hurriyet
reported.  The government can’t say democracy is strengthening in
Turkey when people are under surveillance, Kilicdaroglu said,
according to the Istanbul-based newspaper. “Even my children’s
mobile phones are being tapped,” he said.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
